mixin article()
  -
    const tagList = [
      "#VRDesign",
      "#ArchitectureInnovation",
      "#VirtualRealityArchitecture",
      "#BringingDesignsToLife",
      "#DesignVisualization",
      "#ArchitecturalVisualization",
      "#RevolutionizingArchitecture",
      "#BuildingInVR",
      "#DesignThinking",
      "#VRInArchitecture",
    ]

  .article
    +badge({text: "VR Architecture"}).article__badge
    +title({tag: "h3", text: "Bringing Designs to Life: How VR is Changing Architecture", mods: ["h3"]}).article__title
    .article__publication-data
      p
        | Nasyiya Ulfa |
        time(pubdate datetime="2022-11-25") 25 Nov 2022
    .article__picture
      +picture("content", "article-pic-1", "jpg", 789, 528, "In VR")
    p!= "Architecture is&nbsp;an&nbsp;art and science that is&nbsp;constantly evolving with technology. The industry has gone through various transformations over the years, from pencil and paper sketches to&nbsp;computer-aided design (CAD) software. However, one technology that is&nbsp;revolutionizing architecture is&nbsp;virtual reality (VR) design."
    p!= "With VR&nbsp;design, architects can bring their designs to&nbsp;life and offer clients an&nbsp;immersive experience that was previously impossible. The technology enables architects to&nbsp;create a&nbsp;virtual representation of&nbsp;their designs, allowing clients to&nbsp;step into the building and explore its features and spaces before it&nbsp;is&nbsp;built."
    p!= "VR&nbsp;design is&nbsp;a&nbsp;game-changer for architects and clients alike. It&nbsp;enables architects to&nbsp;design with a&nbsp;greater level of&nbsp;detail and precision, allowing them to&nbsp;identify design flaws and make necessary modifications before construction begins. This not only saves time and money but also ensures that the final product meets the client&rsquo;s expectations."
    p!= "Clients can also benefit from&nbsp;VR design by&nbsp;having a&nbsp;better understanding of&nbsp;the design and how it&nbsp;will look and feel in&nbsp;real life. It&nbsp;allows them to&nbsp;experience the design in&nbsp;a&nbsp;more realistic way, helping them make informed decisions and providing valuable feedback to&nbsp;the architects."
    p!= "Moreover, VR&nbsp;design is&nbsp;not only limited to&nbsp;the design phase. It&nbsp;can also be&nbsp;used in&nbsp;the construction process to&nbsp;visualize the project&rsquo;s progress and identify any issues that may arise."
    .article__picture-wrapper
      .article__picture.article__picture--left
        +picture("content", "video-poster-mobile", "jpg", 398, 254, "Some alt text")
      .article__picture.article__picture--right
        +picture("content", "head-mounted-display-3", "jpg", 377, 252, "Some alt text")
    p!= "The benefits of&nbsp;VR design in&nbsp;architecture are clear, and the technology is&nbsp;becoming increasingly accessible and affordable. More and more architects and firms are incorporating&nbsp;VR design into their workflows, and the industry is&nbsp;poised for a&nbsp;major transformation."
    p!= "In&nbsp;conclusion, VR&nbsp;design is&nbsp;changing the way architects design and bring their projects to&nbsp;life. It&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;powerful tool that offers a&nbsp;range of&nbsp;benefits, from increased precision and efficiency in&nbsp;the design phase to&nbsp;better communication and understanding with clients. As&nbsp;the technology becomes more advanced and widespread, we&nbsp;can expect to&nbsp;see more innovative designs and better-designed buildings in&nbsp;the future."
    .article__list-wrapper
      +title({tag: "h4", text: "Post &nbsp;Tags&nbsp;:", mods: ["h10"]}).article__list-title
      ul.article__tag-list
        each tag in tagList
          li.article__tag!= tag
    .article__list-wrapper
      +title({tag: "h4", text: "Share", mods: ["h10"]}).article__list-title
      +socials([
        {iconName: "icon-tw", href: "#/", label: "Twitter"},
        {iconName: "icon-fb",href: "#/", label: "Facebook"},
        {iconName: "icon-ig", href: "#/", label: "Instagram"},
      ], true)




